snippet.title: Paris 11th Arrondissement - 20 in 20 Day 11 - Oberkampf Market and Melt BBQ
snippet.description:
Paris' 11th arrondissement is the place to go for good food and social life. Whether it's markets, restaurants, or rooftop bars, it's a great spot to land. Grab my guide to Paris here: http://bit.ly/ParisVloggersGuide for all of my recommendations in the 11th district of Paris along with all the rest.

Help me make better videos at http://patreon.com/jayswanson and then find me on the internet in all of the usual spots:


More swag here:
http://bit.ly/ShirtOfTheMonth (shirts and hat)
http://bit.ly/JaysGearList (my gear and books)
https://gum.co/camerafour (Disposable Camera Four digital scans)

Follow me here:
http://twitter.com/jayonaboat
http://instagram.com/jayswanson

Music by: David Cutter Music - http://www.davidcuttermusic.co.uk

My name is Jay Swanson - I'm an American writer living in Paris on an artist visa and hoping to make the city of light my home base - at least for the foreseeable future. I write science-fiction and fantasy, vlog daily, and love pizza a little too much.

Links below to Amazon are affiliate links - meaning if you click through them and buy something, I'll get some pennies. Thanks! (The FTC wants me to tell you that up front)

FAQ:
How long have you lived in France? On and off for over two years.

What do you miss most about ho- NACHOS

You're always talking about living on some ship. WHAT SHIP? - I made a "Draw My Life" video that explains a lot here: https://youtu.be/-MrvL37jTKM

Where are you from originally? - Pullman, Washington - a small university/agricultural town near Idaho (and yes, the potatoes are amazing).

What do you film with? - I've made a lot of changes recently, but I try to keep my gear list up to date if you want to see what I use and buy some for yourself: http://bit.ly/JaysGearList

What do you edit with? - Adobe Premiere - it's pretty much all I've ever used since high school.

Aren't you ever freaked out by leaving your camera behind to film yourself? - Yep. But not too badly - I tend to be careful when I do.

Why are you living in #Paris? - Because I've always wanted to; I feel at home here: https://youtu.be/4Vivf6MqMxQ

Do you speak French? Oui. https://youtu.be/va1QjaHgij8

You talk a lot about the books you're working on, what are they about? - They're sci-fi (and fantasy) and I've got a decent pitch for you here: https://youtu.be/W2bKt4_Tp4E

Do you make money off YouTube? - Ha, no. I wish. It took me over 500 videos to make my first total $100 off adsense. I think it will slowly change, but VERY slowly.

I really enjoy your videos, how can I support you? - The easiest and best way to support me is through Patreon, where you can pitch in as little as $1/mo to help me make better videos: http://patreon.com/jayswanson

I don't trust this Patreon thing - can I just paypal you? - Here's my ko-fi if that's your thing (and coffee is your game): https://ko-fi.com/jayswanson

But I want to send you something tangible! - I do have a wishlist on Amazon, though it's a bit complicated with the international shipping situation. This is the US one: http://amzn.to/2ykS9Ux

And here's the French wishlist: http://bit.ly/JaysFrenchWishList

Thanks for watching!

comments.textDisplay: The 11th definitely feels like a Parisian’s Paris to me. Good to see the Bataclan. I saw Three Doors Down and Seether there. It’s super hard to think about November 13, 2015. There were several restaurants in the 10th that were affected, too. “Affected.” I guess “attacked” is more accurate... I’m glad the Bataclan has reopened and may such things never happen again. ✌🏼

replies.textDisplay: +Hazel Hoyte Well, is a little bit more than that. They did an amazing job not only recreating the painting but animating certain details of the painting bringing it up to life. I don't understand why people take little kids to these kinds of shows.

I love spotting places that we've been by on our visits....we definitely walked past Le Cafe Des Chats. We were moving over to a bar La Fée Vert in the 11th. It was listed as a belle epoque era establishment the specialized in absinthe.

Who knew we were so close to such tasty coffee at Paul et Rimbaud.

comments.textDisplay: Wondered through the Bastille market last week; All the fish you could possibly want.  And scarves, hand bags, fruit and veggies, hot food, soup to nuts. More importantly, found a terrific bar where the vendors gatherer after work.   A lovely dog named Leenda or so the cook helpfully offered, when we took over petting duties. It sounds like that, but probably is something else, because it was a guy dog. Tables full of tired working people, getting some food and drink, and happily telling stories and catching up with their mates.  Gawd, what a wonderful place.

comments.textDisplay: If anyone is visiting Paris in the next couple of months or so I highly recommend the Atelier des Lumieres in Rue Saint Maur. They currently have a digital art exhibition on Van Gogh which is AMAZING. Totally immersive. Just down the street from St Ambroise. My friend & I had lunch in that park afterwards.
